OL,6,F"They tell you 'you owe them the
OL,7,Fmoney, you owe them'.
OL,9,F"They always use the word, 'we brought
OL,10,Fyou to the UK and you owe us this
OL,11,Fmoney'."
OL,13,FIn a bid to try and pay off his debt,
OL,14,FMichael began working 16 hour days
OL,15,Fwhich he found "draining" both
OL,16,Fmentally and physically.
OL,18,F"You wake up at 4am, that's when you
OL,19,Fstart your day. You work from 4pm all
OL,20,Fthe way to about 10pm before you get
OL,21,Fback home.
